            "answer_text": "We recently released our brand-new ultrabook, HONOR MagicBook Pro, which is fit a massive 16.1-inch screen inside the standard 15.6-inch chassis, for a sky-high screen-to-body ratio of 90%.  You're probably wondering how it's possible that this laptop measures almost the same as a traditional 15.6 inches laptop, but manages to house a 16.1-inch screen.  The answer is - we've upped that to 16.1 inches, by sealing the screen in a novel way, packing in a recessed camera, and relocating the screen controller boards.  A new method for sealing the laptop screen With a conventional design, the screen is sealed onto the bezels along the edges, with bumpers integrated into between to lessen the impact from external shocks. This leads to a whole lot of wasted space around the screen. The designers behind the all-new MagicBook Pro opted to place the seal on the back of the screen, to slim down the bezels to a remarkable degree - the upper bezel and side bezels are reduced to an incredible 4.9mm. At the same time, although MagicBook Pro uses all these innovative screen sealing technologies, the overall screen quality keeps at the same level as those traditional laptops, and successfully passed the strict quality test in HONOR Lab. The pop-up webcam which hidden within the keyboard The recessed camera is hardly a new feature on an HONOR laptop. It is hidden within the keyboard, disguised as a key when not in use, and only pops up when pressed. This frees up more space for the screen and safeguards privacy. By contrast, traditional webcams render a significant amount of upper bezel space unusable, and can leave users vulnerable to peeping or spying from malicious actors. A new location for the screen controller boards The lower bezel is usually the thickest within the frame, because it houses all of the controller boards that the screen monitor needs. On the HONOR MagicBook Pro though, our engineers have relocated some of the boards, ingeniously hiding them within the hinge, reducing the lower bezel height to an inconceivable 14.6mm.  The benefits of a larger screen are obvious and wide-ranging \u2013 more productive multitasking, easier laptop-phone interactions, as well as more immersive gaming and binge-watching. Even still, the MagicBook Pro maintains a sleek and compact form, making it the perfect companion for users who are often on-the-go, and inclined to take it to class, to the office, or on outings. To learn more information and find the best offer, click HONOR MagicBook Pro Germany, HONOR MagicBook Pro UK, HONOR MagicBook Pro France, HONOR MagicBook Pro Italy, HONOR MagicBook Pro Spain, HONOR MagicBook Pro Netherlands, HONOR MagicBook Pro Russia About us: HONOR is the leading technology brand of the HUAWEI Group for Global Youth. Check more info via HONOR Mobile Phones. Please upvote and follow us to learn more about smartphones, wearables, and IoTs. ",
